An article ART. precedes each noun phrase in hul'q'umi'num'. The basic articles are as follows: masculine unmarked.: tthu visible, unmarked., kwthu nonvisible, remote., kw' hypothetical, deceased.; feminine marked.: thu visible, unmarked., lhu nonvisible, remote., kws hypothetical, deceased. There is considerable variation in the use of feminine articles, Words denoting feminine persons or things require a feminine article unless they are plural.

A contraction of tthu + 'uw'-nilh, referring to someone or something previously mentioned.  'uw'-nilh combines with the other articles as well cf, thuw'nilh, that-one feminine. These may precede a noun phrase like an article or stand alone.
